queue module¶

class containers.queue.Queue(elements=None)¶

Bases: object

Queue data structure.

Parameters:elements (list) – list of elements (optional)

Examples

>>> q1 = Queue()
>>> q2 = Queue([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])
>>> print(q1)
[]
>>> print(q2)
[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
clear()¶

Clear all elements from the queue.

Examples

>>> q1 = Queue([1, 2, 3])
>>> q1.clear()
>>> print(q1)
[]
dequeue()¶
Pop first element off queue and return.
Returns None if queue is empty.

Examples

>>> q1 = Queue([1, 2, 3])
>>> v1 = q1.dequeue()
>>> print(v1)
1
>>> print(q1)
[2, 3]
Returns:first element in queue or None
Return type:mixed
enqueue(value)¶

Inserts a new value to the end of the queue.

Parameters:value (mixed) – new element

Examples

>>> q1 = Queue([1, 2, 3])
>>> q1.enqueue(4)
>>> print(q1)
[1, 2, 3, 4]
isEmpty()¶

Checks if queue is empty.

Examples

>>> q1 = Queue([1, 2, 3])
>>> v1 = q1.isEmpty()
>>> print(v1)
False
>>> q2 = Queue()
>>> v2 = q2.isEmpty()
>>> print(v2)
True
Returns:True or False
Return type:bool
peek()¶
Preview first element in queue.
Only returns None if queue is empty.

Examples

>>> q1 = Queue([1, 2, 3])
>>> v1 = q1.peek()
>>> print(v1)
1
>>> q2 = Queue()
>>> v2 = q2.peek()
>>> print(v2)
None
Returns:first element in queue or None
Return type:mixed
